http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/kerala/SBT-staff-ask-government-to-drop-merger-move-with-SBI/article14596327.ece

The State Bank of Travancore Employees Union, affiliated to the All India Bank Employees Association (AIBEA), has asked the Union government to stop merging State Bank of Travancore (SBT) and other associate banks with State Bank of India (SBI).The union has asked the State government to consider the views of the people and people’s representatives from Kerala. A resolution adopted here on Sunday, marking the conclusion of a two-day meeting of the union, pointed out that the management was hurrying with the merger in spite of the public opinion being against it. The SBI management has announced that nearly 7,000 bank branches will have to be either closed or relocated with the merger. The union blamed the management for sacrificing national priorities and mass banking in the name of creating a global bank.The staff union has asked the State government to consider the views of the people.